Welcome to MiNTOS Release 1.4.1
-------------------------------

This is still a development version of this package, and as such there is
little documentation (at least until I've learnt how to use the nroff man
package). If anyone wants to offer their services in this respect, I'd be
greatful. In the mean time, as Eric Smith says, "Use the source Luke!".

Essentially, most of the programs are very much like their BSD equivalents,
within the limitations of MiNT, indeed many ARE the BSD versions.

In the "etc" directory I've included example start-up files, including those
for popular shells such as tcsh, ash and Bash.

If you have any bug fixes, bug reports etc. don't hesitate to contact me.
Hopefully we can build this package into something which makes MiNT usable
as a true multi-user system.

Anyway, have a play and have fun!

